18/05/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Prime Minister Ivo Sanader met on Monday (17 May) with the leaders of four main opposition parties to discuss key political issues.
The opposition parties included the Social Democratic Party, the Croatian Peasants Party, the Croatian People's Party and the Croatian Party of Rights.
The participants discussed the country's EU integration process, the possible start of accession talks with the Union and co-operation with the war crimes tribunal in The Hague.
Also Monday, foreign ministers of EU countries met in Brussels and announced that the European Commission's avis on Croatia would be discussed next month at the European Council summit.
Croatia hopes to get candidate status and a date for the start of accession talks by the end of this year or the beginning of 2005.
(Vecernji List, Vjesnik - 18/05/04;
HINA - 17/05/04)
